# 🐞 bug report

### Description

<!-- ✍️-->  
The view gets parsed before `ngOnInit` is finished if there is async code in the `ngOnInit`, it thinks the ngOnInit is finished and starts parsing the view. I've already asked this on 
[StackOverflow](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/53925659/angular-material-table-typeerror-cannot-read-property-cars-of-undefined), which includes a rich description of the issue. 

Basically I have a function: 
<pre><code>   async ngOnInit() {
    console.log('before getting cars: ');
    console.log(this.cars);
    this.cars = await this.carService.getCars().toPromise();
    console.log('got cars:');
    console.log(this.cars);
    this.dataSource = new CarsTableDataSource(this.paginator, this.sort, this.cars);
  }
</pre></code>
which awaits some objects from a database and then sets a `dataSource` for a table, but there is an error on this line of the html:
<pre><code>[length]="dataSource.cars.length"
</pre></code>
The error happens, because the dataSource is undefined (uninitialized during parsing of template). The template gets parsed after it sees the `await` in the `ngOnInit`
